Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 20:35:00 -0700
Subject: [FAILED EXPERIMENT] Keep ESM4 actor KF sampling out of the extra native basis

The ESM4 manual actor animation composer already applies the actor skeleton
local basis while composing pose matrices. Letting the native NIF controller
also apply the Fallout actor half-turn basis can invert or explode live actor
geometry when current/auto skinning is enabled.

Keep source skinning as the default containment fallback. This patch only makes
the current/auto experiment defensible by sampling NifOsg keyframes without the
extra native Fallout actor basis in the manual composer path.

Experiment result:

- Build: passed against D:\Modlists\fnv\openmw-source on 2026-07-07.
- Runtime proof: failed.
- Evidence: run/proof-harness-sweeps/20260707-203118/summary.md.
- Result: current/auto still fail FO3 and FNV actor proof-status rows with
  actor-pose-invalid and rig-pose failures. Do not list this patch in
  patches/openmw/series unless a later patch also proves the complete actor
  basis/skinning fix.
